Results: AEW/ROH Jay Briscoe Tribute Show
AEW
Announcers Ian Riccaboni and Caprice Coleman opened the show talking about Jay Briscoe
Tony Khan came out and thanked the fans for being there to honor Briscoe’s legacy
Wheeler Yuta def. Hagane Shinno to retain the ROH Pure Wrestling Championship – The judges at ringside were Jerry Lynn, Dean Malenko and BJ Whitmer, but it didn’t go to the judges
Adam Cole came out and talked about his memories of Jay Briscoe – Cole said Jay would smack him in the back of the head right now and tell him to “man up and have a badass wrestling show”
Marina Shafir def. Mighty Myra
Eddie Kingston def. QT Marshall
Athena def. Madison Rayne w/Skye Blue – Athena attacked Blue after the match
Juice Robinson def. Brandon Cutler
Yuka Sakazaki def. Sandra Moone
Claudio Castagnoli def. Christopher Daniels to retain the ROH World Championship
Daniels and Castagnoli both spoke about Briscoe and his passing

Backstage News On AEW's Jay Briscoe Celebration Of Life Tribute Show
Cindy Ord/Getty Images
ByRobert Gunier/Jan. 19, 2023 12:52 pm EST
In the aftermath of the tragic passing of Jay Briscoe on Tuesday night, AEW and ROH owner Tony Khan began brainstorming ways to do a proper tribute show. However,PWInsiderhas confirmed that AEW was limited in what it could do on "Dynamite" last night because its broadcast partner, WarnerMedia, didn't want Jay and Mark Briscoe on AEW programming in the past.

Celebration of LifeThe Jay Briscoe Tribute and Celebration of Life premiered on the ROH YouTube channel.The show was held in honor of Jay Briscoe (Jamin Pugh), a 13-time ROH World Champion who lost his life in a car accident on January 17. Ring of Honor taped the special on January 18 from theSave Mart Center in Fresno, CA.AEW has released a Jay Briscoe memorial shirt, and all proceeds will go to the Pugh family.
